Image source: © Ion Chiosea – 123RF.comThrough its collected data, the recruitment agency found that Covid-19 and the resultant crisis continued to severely impact employment statistics with a downturn in hiring during 2021. "Employers were cautious about employing new staff with a strong message to maintaining cash flow and consolidating their core business," Ad Talent said in its statement. "We noticed a trend to employ on short term contracts with a view to permanent employment at a later stage. There was a lack of confidence to commit to long term projects with a conservative approach to hiring."The agency found that this resulted to salary stagnation in most categories with a few exceptions. "Salary progression in the form of increases was largely on hold with little or no movement and in some instances, salary cuts were applied. We found that many candidates who were previously looking for a career change, put a halt on their search because of the instability in the job market," said the recruiter.It did however see a slight increase in salaries and more benefits at senior level, and attributed this to the retention of top talent.As in previous years, Ad Talent's Salary Survey was compiled: using figures of actual placements made by Ad Talent using figures from salary information obtained from all candidates interviewed by Ad Talent from January 2021 to December 2021 using figures from salary information obtained from candidates who have submitted their CVs to Ad Talent using cost to company (CTC) figures using the average salaries per sectorInterpretation: Salaries vary significantly depending on many factors, including size of the company, desirability to work for a particular company and status Salaries for media sales roles vary significantly depending on the commission structure / incentives 0-2 years (light) means 0 to 2 years experience in that particular position and not 0 to 2 years total working experience The same applies for medium and heavy weight. It is experience in the particular position and NOT total working experience This survey is not intended to be prescriptive, but is a report on what we, Ad Talent, (not the entire industry) has experienced in the past 12 monthsSee the full results of the Ad Talent Salary Survey 2022 below:Advertising Agencies0-2 yrs (light)2 – 5 yrs (medium)5 – 9 yrs (heavyweight)Managing DirectorJohannesburgR90 000 – R100 000R100 000 – R150 000R150 000+Cape TownR75 000 – R90 000R90 000 – R130 000R130 000+Deputy MDJohannesburgR85 000 – R94 000R94 000 – R100 000R100 000+Cape TownR75 000 – R84 000R84 000 – R93 000R93 000+Client Service/Business Unit DirectorJohannesburgR56 000 – R60 000R60 000 – R66 000R66 000+Cape TownR48 000 – R55 000R55 000 – R60 000R60 000+Group Account DirectorJohannesburgR49 000 – R54 000R54 000 – R60 000R60 000+Cape TownR45 000 – R50 000R50 000 – R55 000R55 000+Account DirectorJohannesburgR36 000 – R41 000R41 000 – R50 000N/ACape TownR35 000 – R40 000R40 000 – R46 000N/AAccount ManagerJohannesburgR24 000 – R27 000R27 000 – R36 000N/ACape TownR18 000 – R20 000R20 000 – R30 000N/AAccount ExecutiveJohannesburgR15 000 – R18 000R18 000 – R21 000N/ACape TownR12 000 – R15 000R15 000 – R17 000N/AProject ManagerJohannesburgR27 000 – R40 000R40 000 – R45 000R45 000+Cape TownR23 000 – R30 000R30 000 – R40 000R40 000+OperationsJohannesburgR49 000 – R60 000R60 000 – R80 000R80 000+Cape TownR45 000 – R57 000R57 000 – R70 000R70 000+ProductionJohannesburgR14 000 – R22 000R22 000 – R40 000R40 000+Cape TownR12 000 – R20 000R20 000 – R35 000R35 000+TrafficJohannesburgR15 000 – R20 000R20 000 – R37 000R37 000+Cape TownR15 000 – R17 000R17 000 – R35 000R35 000+Strategic Planning DirectorJohannesburgR63 000 – R70 000R70 000 – R89 000R89 000+Cape TownR55 000 – R68 000R68 000 – R85 000R85 000+Strategic PlannerJohannesburgR18 000 – R30 000R30 000 – R47 000R47 000+Cape TownR15 000 – R25 000R25 000 – R40 000R40 000+Digital0-2 yrs (light)2 – 5 yrs (medium)5 – 9 yrs (heavyweight)Strateg